featured_reviews.review_id: Spacious mosque. Three floors. Ground floor is air conditioned. Jumma prayers starts at 13.35 pm. On Jumma try being in the mosque before 1 pm if you want to be in the ground floor area. Else the other three floors can be accessed even untill 13.25 pm. Ramzan time has 2 Jamaats for Jumma . First one at 13.35 hrs and second jamaat at 14.00 hrs. A beautiful and peaceful place to pray. However, the trustees can do much better. But keep your visit related to praying in peace and make duaa for the entire Ummaah.

featured_reviews.review_id:
It's located in Chandivali
People have taken huge efforts to build it I believe
Inside of the premises is made of all marble
Muslims who work around this area enjoin for prayers in this Masjid, especially for Juma prayer
Masjid in Arabic/Urdu (Mosque in English) is a place of Worship in Islaam
Devotees offer/perform 5 times prayers everyday (namely Fajr, Dhuhr, A'sr, Maghrib, E'shaa)
Also, Juma' prayer, Eid Prayers, all prayers are performed in congregation
This is Hanafi Masjid (Hanafi school of thoughts) one of the four schools of thoughts (namely Hanafi, Shafai', Hambali, Maliki)
Masjid is managed by Trust
Trustees are also committed towards the overall management of Trust
Masjid's cleanliness/hygiene of the place is optimum, giving the in coming crowd an extremely nice experience of worshiping.
Toilets are good, spacious
Very nice & tidy, few you get to see in Mumbai/India
Cleanliness staff are hard working & fulfilling their duty

featured_reviews.review_id:
Chand Shah Wali Dargah, nestled within the serene forests of Aarey Colony in Goregaon East, is a hidden gem that offers a peaceful escape from the bustling city life. This sacred site is a testament to the rich cultural and historical heritage of the region.

The dargah itself is a simple yet beautifully maintained structure, exuding an aura of tranquility. Surrounded by lush greenery, it provides a calming atmosphere for visitors seeking solace and spiritual reflection.

What makes Chand Shah Wali Dargah truly special is its unique location within the Aarey Colony forests. The journey to reach the dargah involves a serene walk amidst the trees and wildlife, providing a sense of communion with nature. This makes it a perfect spot for those who appreciate the combination of spirituality and natural beauty.

The dargah is well-maintained, and devotees and tourists alike can find moments of quiet contemplation here. Visitors often offer prayers and light candles, creating a serene and mystical ambiance.

However, it's essential to be respectful of the religious significance of this site and follow any rules or guidelines provided by the caretakers. Additionally, due to its location within the forest, it's advisable to check the accessibility and visitation hours in advance, as they may vary.

In summary, Chand Shah Wali Dargah in Goregaon East, located amidst the enchanting Aarey Colony forests, is a place of spiritual significance and natural beauty. Whether you seek a spiritual experience or a peaceful retreat from city life, this dargah offers a unique and tranquil setting that's worth exploring.
